                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d44">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00112 European War 1939/1573: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sterling</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-05-09T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 9, 1940—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>140. Your 434, May 3, 5 p.m. We have instituted no negotiations of the character
                    referred to in your telegram. Should the Swedish Government, however, approach
                    the British, French and German Governments with a view to facilitating the
                    resumption of Swedish sailings between the United States and Sweden we might
                    feel warranted in supporting the Swedish representations through an approach of
                    our own based on the adverse effect upon American commerce caused by the present
                    situation.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
